{"type":null,"faqId":36210,"title":"My phone often disconnects from the Wi-Fi network on its own","answer":"<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Restart the Wi-Fi hotspot, for example, the wireless router.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Turn the Wi-Fi switch off and then back on again.</p>\n<p style='margin: 4pt 0in 4pt 106.3pt; line-height: 12pt; text-indent: -21.25pt; font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt; -ms-layout-grid-mode: char; tab-stops: list 106.3pt;'><span style=\"top: -1pt; font-family: Wingdings; font-size: 8pt; position: relative;\"><span>l<span style='font: 7pt/normal \"Times New Roman\"; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal;'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span>Restart your phone.</p>\n<span style='font-family: \"Times New Roman\",\"serif\"; font-size: 10.5pt;'>Check whether the\nwireless router is set to hide the SSID. If so, the network must be added\nmanually. Select <b>Add network...</b> in\nthe Wi-Fi settings and enter the network SSID following the on-screen prompts.\nPlease refer to the wireless router instructions for a detailed description of\nthe settings.</span>","faqTypeId":null,"faqType":null,"useful":1,"unUseful":3,"languageId":1,"langua